Brie Larson Doubles Down – Wants Fewer White Men on Captain Marvel Press Tour

Captain Marvel actress Brie Larson doubled down on her views of press coverage. She indicated she wants fewer white men covering her Captain Marvel press tour.

Larson sat down with Keah Brown for Marie Claire to reiterate her position on white men when it comes to her Captain Marvel press tour.

“About a year ago, I started paying attention to what my press days looked like and the critics…

summary: look, when Captain Marvel does well I don’t wanna hear any “Marvel released it in a bad box office month because they wanted it...
body:
look, when Captain Marvel does well I don’t wanna hear any “Marvel released it in a bad box office month because they wanted it to fail” BS like I heard with Black Panther, aight.

Black Panther was released during Black History Month. Captain Marvel is being released during Women’s History Month. Avengers Endgame is being released during April Fool’s Month so we all know that whatever happens in it is “jk, no one’s dead we just messing with you.”

Marvel knows what they’re doing okay.

summary: i am PRAYING that captain marvel is good because from the trailers so far its really a 50/50 game rn. she looks badass but the...
body:
i am PRAYING that captain marvel is good because from the trailers so far its really a 50/50 game rn. she looks badass but the delivery of some of her lines (esp. “i’m gonna end it”) is very valley-girl-esque which could delegitimize her. add that to the worry that endgame will feature captain-marvel-ex-machina and you have yourself a mary sue. from some of the tv spots that have actual dialogue, she’s silly and serious in equal amounts (characterizing/humanizing/showing flaws) so there’s still hope. i really want this movie to be good!!!

clarifying: IM REALLY HYPED FOR THIS MOVIE AND WILL SPEND ALL MY MONEY ON IT i just really hope its good so the butthurt fanboys can shut up
